# Reactive Rules

Rules live in the app tiddler's body text (the `text` field). They define cascading channel updates — when one channel changes, others are automatically set.

## Syntax

```
<$statewrap-rule when="project">
  <$action-statewrap-set channel="task" value=""/>
  <$action-statewrap-set channel="tab" value="overview"/>
</$statewrap-rule>
```

This means: when the "project" channel changes, clear "task" and reset "tab" to "overview".

## Common patterns

### Master-detail reset
When selecting a new project, clear the task selection and reset tabs:
```
<$statewrap-rule when="project">
  <$action-statewrap-set channel="task" value=""/>
  <$action-statewrap-set channel="tab" value="overview"/>
</$statewrap-rule>
```

### Cascade reset
When a mid-level selection changes, reset downstream:
```
<$statewrap-rule when="task">
  <$action-statewrap-set channel="tab" value="overview"/>
</$statewrap-rule>
```

## Modifying rules

1. Read the app tiddler's text field (get_tiddler)
2. Edit the `<$statewrap-rule>` blocks
3. Write back with set_field(field="text")

Multiple rules are just sequential blocks in the body text.

## Adding a rule for a new channel

If you add a channel "theme", you might want:
```
<$statewrap-rule when="theme">
  <$action-statewrap-set channel="tab" value="overview"/>
</$statewrap-rule>
```

Append this to the existing body text.

